# Grammar test fixtures (`.sd`) are read byte-for-byte by the snapshot tests,
# and the `.snap` / `.vsc.snap` baselines are generated on LF checkouts. Force
# LF for both on every platform so the snapshot suites are byte-stable
# regardless of `core.autocrlf` — without this, a Windows checkout rewrites the
# fixtures to CRLF and every newline-bearing snapshot diffs (`"\r\n"` vs
# `"\n"`, span lengths off by one per line). See GRAMMAR.md §17.
*.sd    text eol=lf
*.snap  text eol=lf
